# Claude Code Conventions

## Memory and Context
- Project context is in `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root
- Rule files live in `.claude/rules/` (loaded automatically)
- Never read `CLAUDE.md` manually — Claude Code loads it on session start

## MCP Servers
{% if mcp_servers %}
Configured MCP servers: {{ mcp_servers | join(', ') }}
{% else %}
No MCP servers configured. Add them to `.claude/mcp.json` with the `"mcpServers"` key.
{% endif %}

## File Writing
- Use `Write` tool for new files
- Use `Edit` tool (string replacement) for existing files — never overwrite large files
- Prefer `TodoWrite` for multi-step tasks to track progress

## Code Style
- Follow existing patterns in the codebase
- Match indentation and naming conventions of surrounding code
- Do not add comments explaining what code does — code should be self-documenting
